{"SEAL":[{"def":"Any aquatic carnivorous mammal of the families Phocidæ and Otariidæ.","pos":""}],"SEAL-BROWN":[{"def":"Of a rich dark brown color, like the fur of the fur seal after it is dyed.","pos":""}],"SEALER":[{"def":"One who seals; especially, an officer whose duty it is to seal writs or instruments, to stamp weights and measures, or the like.","pos":""}],"SEALING WAX":[{"def":"A compound of the resinous materials, pigments, etc.","pos":""}],"SEALSKIN":[{"def":"The skin of a seal; the pelt of a seal prepared for use, esp.","pos":""}]}